      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "> This is supported. [We currently have a \"Coverage\" build type](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/blob/master/CMakeLists.txt#L158)...\n\nThe following is an example workflow on Ubuntu 24.04:\n```\ncmake -B build -DCMAKE_GENERATOR=Ninja -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Coverage\ncmake --build build  # Ninja uses all available cores by default\nctest --test-dir build -j $(nproc)\nmkdir -p build/coverage\ngcovr --merge-mode-functions=separate --exclude 'src/bench*' --html --html-details -o build/coverage/coverage.html\nfirefox build/coverage/coverage.html\n```\n> ... but we figured out that using a build type (like Release, Debug, ...) may be the wrong approach because it results in issues with CMake multi-config generators.\n\nFor the multi-config generators, please see an example in https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/pull/1592#issuecomment-3172792969.",
